item.title: Copper Weakens Ahead of China Central Bank Meeting
item.description: Copper prices slipped and other base metals were mixed, as traders nervously awaited a Chinese central bank meeting on Tuesday at which officials are broadly expected to cut interest rates to support the economy following a stretch of weak data releases.

item.title: SVB Securities to Be Acquired in Management Buyout
item.description: The investment-banking business tied to Silicon Valley Bank will go back to being called Leerink Partners.

item.title: FTSE 100 Falls After Asia Stocks Decline
item.description: The FTSE 100 fell 0.3% in early trading, tracking declines in Asian equities as concerns over China’s economic outlook weighed on sentiment.

item.title: Oil Dips on China Growth Fears
item.description: Oil prices fell as investors continued to worry about the Chinese economy, with recent weak data undermining hopes that China’s postpandemic recovery would boost demand for crude.

item.title: RBC Advises Selling Euro Vs Sterling Ahead of BOE Decision
item.description: Sterling could rise as the BOE’s meeting Thursday might prompt the market to raise its U.K. interest rate expectations, RBC Capital Markets said, advising selling EUR/GBP, targeting 0.8370 and placing a stop loss at 0.8600.

item.title: Michelin Buys High-Tech Fabrics Engineer
item.description: Michelin has acquired Flex Composite from private-equity firm IDI for €700 million, expecting the deal to gradually increase its underlying earnings margin.

item.title: Ten-Year Bund Yield Seen Falling Toward Bottom of Range In Coming Months
item.description: Ten-year German Bund yields are expected to fall to the lower end of the 2%-2.5% trading range over the coming months, Morgan Stanley said, affirming its previous expectations.

item.title: MTU Aero Lifts Operating Margin Guidance
item.description: MTU Aero Engines said it expected adjusted earnings for 2023 above €800 million, equivalent to a slight increase in the 12.3% margin it booked last year, based on expectations regarding its future business development.

item.title: Tech-Stock Boom Pits AI Against the Fed
item.description: Investors can’t agree on whether the rally looks like a repeat of 1999 or the start of something bigger.

item.title: Ukraine's Offensive Is a Battle of Readiness
item.description: The coming battles with Russian troops ultimately will boil down to which side has better prepared and strengthened over recent months.

item.title: These Businesses Are Getting Hit Hard by China's Faltering Economic Recovery
item.description: The government in Beijing has pushed banks to extend loans to small businesses, with limited success.

item.title: Rio Tinto Says Driverless Iron-Ore Train Derailed in Western Australia
item.description: Rio Tinto said an autonomous train carrying iron ore from its mining operations in remote northwest Australia to a port derailed late Saturday.
